    <description>The experimental arm will have an IV infusion of glulisine insulin started directly after randomization for at least 24 hours and for as long as CCU-level care is required, and the insulin infusion will be adjusted to achieve and maintain a target glucose range of 5.0-6.6 mmol/L (90-118 mg/dL). Once transferred to the ward, patients in the experimental arm will switch to glargine insulin and will continue this treatment for the remainder of their hospitalization and after hospital discharge, for a total duration of 30 days post randomization.</description>
